Minha mãe trabalhou duro demaaais, foi camelô (vendedora ambulante) no centro de Manaus, vendia dindin(sacolé, geladinho), vendia cartão de natal, dava aula de reforço pra criar eu e minhas irmãs sozinha, acredito que no fundo É ISSO QUE SEMPRE ME MOTIVA: CONTINUAR APRENDENDO. 
Mais um curso para preencher no meu currículo e eu estou apaixonada. Finalizei esse final de semana 125 horas de curso teórico e prático INTENSIVO E COMPLETO DE PILATES 🧘🏻‍♀️🤸🏻‍♀️ e foi pela @vollpilatesgroup que é referência no Brasil ❤️ Eu sempre quero aprender para ser a melhor profissional para os meus alunos, procure um bom profissional porque de aulas montadas via Google e YouTube está cheio. Não caia nessa, procure saber quem é a pessoa que você contrata para ser seu professor, veja se os cursos estão atualizados, se tem a credencial, pois é o seu corpo que será entregue para ser cuidado. Eu quero continuar APRENDENDO SEMPRE e se eu não souber me der algumas horas que eu irei aprender.
Att. Professora Debora Moura 🤩✨🌹

You are the king/queen of your life!

Not the kind of king/queen that fit to what others say and think of how you should be, BUT, your unique way of being you, Free to be and free to act! (this is key!)
-------------------------------------------
Here is what I notice from changing myself so much in the past 5-6 years. People will always have something to say about anything. -------------------------------------------
Basically, from the moment we were born, people were saying things, and then we matured a bit, and people kept saying things, And so on and on until today, people keep saying things!
--------------------------------------------
The truth is, people will never stop saying things, regardless of what you do. --------------------------------------------
You be you and don't let anybody to judge or shame you. I mean, they will keep judging and shaming, and you have nothing to do about it. --------------------------------------------
Be you and don't let it bother you!

text:
"Gib mir die Gelassenheit, hinzunehmen, was ich nicht ändern kann, aber gib mir die Kraft, das zu ändern, was ich ändern kann"
____________________________________________________Darin steckt viel Wahrheit. Ich folge vielen Menschen, die versuchen etwas mit ihrer Reichweite zum positiven zu verändern. Dabei spielen auch Themen wie Mental Health, Body Positivity und Selbstliebe eine Rolle. In den Kommentarsektionen lese ich dann aber immer wieder Dinge wie "Wer dies und jenes macht, kann sich nicht selbst lieben". Dabei werden sowohl Ernährung, Sport aber auch MakeUp und Kleidung genannt. In dieser ganzen "Bewegung" steckt derzeit so viel Bevormundung, dass ich kotzen will. Denn grundsätzlich sagt dir immer jemand, dass du dich nur mögen darfst, wenn x. Wenn du abnehmen willst, akzeptierst du dich nicht, wenn du eine Schönheits-Op willst, liebst du dich nicht, wenn du dich stark schminkst, ist das unnatürlich und du akzeptierst dich nicht. Du kannst nicht Body Positive sein, wenn du schlank bist. Wenn du einen Kartoffelsack anziehst, vernachlässigst du dich... Grundsätzlich hat jeder Mensch viele verschiedene Facetten, die er selbst von gut nach schlecht sortiert, das sind sowohl innere als auch äußere Merkmale. Die Gesamtheit dessen ergibt DICH als Ganzes. Du musst selbst wissen, ob du mit dieser Gesamtheit klar kommst oder nicht. Das hier ist kein Plädoyer für Selbstoptimierung und keines gegen Selbstliebe. Aber es wird einem unheimlich schwer gemacht, sich anzunehmen, wenn es immer jemanden gibt, der einem sagt wie man sein muss, damit man sich selbst lieben darf. Ein Mensch muss sich selbst nicht die beste Version seiner Selbst verweigern, um sich selbst zu lieben. Jemand mit kleinen Brüsten zergeht nicht zwingend in Selbsthass, jemand der sich stark schminkt, muss nicht sein Gesicht abscheulich finden. Man kann dennoch den Wunsch nach Veränderung haben. Es gibt immer eine Steigerung des Wohlbefindens.Wie DU sein willst, aussehen, dich annehmen kannst, entscheidest du selbst, nicht die Außenwelt. Diese Dinge tut man für sich, nicht die anderen. Merkt euch das, wenn ihr künftig aburteilt, wer sich selbst liebt oder nicht - diese Kriterien bestimmt jeder selbst

text:
[Shapes of Freedom, 4/6]
... You visualize yourself in a place where there’s no should or must, no age, no matter tiding you up.
You concentrate, your mind dances, still lost but more certain each second of the final goal.
“What did I really want back then ?” The answer is hard to find, it’s blown into pieces and spread all over the hidden place. But it’s right there, a bit everywhere.
Three things, three dreams you really wanted to achieve as a child... Their outlines slowly appear to you. You are drawn to them like a pole to its opposite. But once you see their faces, will you find the power to embrace them ? In a poetic way, any change ressembles a death. Without it, a new part of yourself cannot be born. And death in any form is frightening at the very least...
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
Nothing worth doing is *ever* easy.  Yet, for some reason, we can acknowledge the challenges with just about anything in life and still be supported...except for parenting: the hardest/most important job in the world.  There is a lot of support within our village, but we still have a long way to go to get away from the shame game.  The comments section of any parenting page will readily prove this.  I love motherhood.  It is the most incredible journey I’ve ever been on.  But it’s also the hardest fucking thing I’ve ever done.  If we didn’t love our kids so much, the reality is, parenting wouldn’t be this hard!  I strive to keep things real and relatable on this page - and that’s going to include the beautiful, the good, the bad, and the ugly.  There is no shame in feeling overwhelmed and speaking your truth when things are feeling difficult - and don’t ever let anyone tell you otherwise.  You can feel challenged and overwhelmed, and still be incredibly grateful for your children.  The two are not mutually exclusive.
•
@goldfishandchickennuggets

text:
Day 14

Adventure

As you journey through life a day at a time, don’t discount God’s instructions for your life. —
Hi, my name is Valerie, and I’m a recovering control addict. I believe there’s a few of you out there, so let’s shift together. Today, right now... let’s take look in the mirror at our body and just for a moment think of it’s physical health as if it’s a vehicle and ask it... what adventures are we going to take and how do I best prepare us for the journey of a lifetime? We are given this gift, our very first gift for a purpose. Quite literally I know people with the fanciest cars out there who don’t take care of them, and conversely people with simple vehicles that are super well loved! When you ask your spirit guide this question, literally everything will begin to shift for you! 
What do we control? Damn near everything! We make ourselves  diabetic and put ourselves in little shitty boxes. Why? Maybe fear? Fear of letting go and exploring? Fear of doing it wrong?  shaming Who knows? Maybe ask yourself, why? 
Let’s wrap this back into a conversation about living your best life and health. I receive divine downloads (you might call them symptoms, nudges, reminders) and I have responded to many of them. In fact, one of the biggest nudge lead me to this career of helping other people listen to their downloads and nudges. High blood pressure and weight have lead me through this new journey. 
Here’s what I remind myself and what I want you to remember the next time you get a nudge... it’s imperative that you respond IMMEDIATELY (yes, I’m yelling) to the messaging! Listen when the lights go on and the reminder is simple, like oil, gas or tire rotation. And avoid letting your vehicle sit in your garage, on the side of the road or on a tow truck. As soon as your body says, hey!!! I’m overwhelmed, over-heating, over-fed & under-nourished... pay attention and do something. 
No matter what, remember obedience and faith is God’s way to the TOP!

text: Brene Brown Took the world by storm with her Ted talk on shame, obtaining millions of views and selling almost as many copies of her books on her shame research. One of the main takeaways I learned from her content was that all shame is bad. It affects your health, psychology, and so forth. But as I observe experiences from my own life and counterbalance that with evolutionary biology, I believe that’s oversimplifying things. I have worked in an organization that screw from 30 to 50 people, and in that time, I’ve observed a few instances where shaming was used to prevent people from doing things that would affect the group, such as leaving food out in the kitchen accidentally. I theorize that shame has been affectively used as a tool for tribes to condition members of the tribe to do things for the benefit of the tribe. Slut shaming may exist because the society didn’t want women to get pregnant before marriage in a time when contraceptives weren’t available, And when society wanted their women to put more thought into who they chose as a partner before consummation. An offshoot of that is slut shaming as a form of female to female competition. The point is that although there are reasons based on evolution that we do things we do, in the modern world, I believe we can achieve the same results with just as much effectiveness without using shame. Some models are outdated and cause more bad side effects than they are worth. It’s similar to Ego. I thought ego was mostly or all bad until I read the Third door by @alexbanayan and Bruce lee a life, and discovered two successful people Tony Hsieh of Zappos and Bruce Lee who used ego effectively. The difference between shaming you go in this case is that ego has its pros and cons in ancient history and the modern times, whereas shame in the modern times only has cons where as it had pros in tribal times.

text:
Some people may remember this post. Well I just wanted to share that I did it, and some. Last week I officially hit -28 lbs which is actually more than what I set out to do. When I put on that weight, anyone super close to me knew how much it impacted me, I really struggled to even look at myself in the mirror, I had no confidence what so ever. From being a a teenager I’ve never been ‘happy’ with my weight. Actually that’s a lie, I was once happy with my weight but no one else was, in fact my best friends mum said “Charlotte you look ill, you’ve lost too much”. I’d say I’ve always just looked “normal” to others, apart from the big gain that I’ve been getting rid of, but my weight is something that is constantly on my mind, every minute of every day. Do I still enjoy a brownie, yes, do I go to the gym, yes. This isn’t an eating disorder, it’s a body image thing. It might not be visible to others at all, but you never know what’s going on inside someone’s head. Some people may read this and think what the hell is she on about she’s never been huge and never been tiny but it’s not about that, it’s about my own self confidence and how I feel in my skin ✌🏻 .
.
.
.

text:
•an unwelcomed post•
•
I used to sit and paint in my room and cry for a different life. And when I finally had freedom, I was fearless in thinking I could “do anything.” Recently I was told, “you are different. And it is off putting to people. Like you’re trying too hard to be different.” And all I could try to explain (and to someone I never thought I’d have to) was that it was just me. Who I am. My genuine self. And while explaining, searching for an approval and a plea of “just love me for this”. Self growth is hard, and remembering your worth is, at times, bittersweet. However, everyday I’m making steps to get back to my fearless self, whether it is embraced or not . But, I think 17 year old Haelee would be very proud of the “different” life she has made.

text:
It's easy to overthink things... Like everything. 🤣🤔 I'm noticing this more and more, weirdly the MORE I schedule time to do the things I need to accomplish for launch day 🚀

I've employed some basic skills that are so so easy to forget. (I had forgotten them till my coach said, hey remember these things??) 1. Analog calendar.  Writing things by hand on something I can see with my own two eyes and touch with my hands makes a huge difference.

2. Scheduled time for  work (max 3 to 4 hour time slots) for maximum productivity and attentiveness. 
3. Scheduled time for  selfcare! Walks, tea, whatever it is, this helps keep the creative spirit alive and my heart open. Decreases drudgery.

4. Remembering  presence. More than anything, I want to enjoy my work and enjoy this process of creation and the journey toward personal freedom and success.

5. Quit  shaming myself! Actually, presence helps with this a ton, as does sticking to my schedule. I enjoy my break time, because I know when work time comes, I will be there, all the way. Shame does nothing for motivation, it's almost like a motivation-killer, and can become a sad feedback loop if we aren't aware of it. 
For those of you who have a  goal in mind, however small (even if it's just getting to your mat!), try employing these small skills. Enjoy your work, even if it's work! Why are we here, if not to enjoy life?

And also, importantly, don't forget to  juststart. Work in the here and now. Work for you first, then for others. It's a beautiful thing.

Xx

text:
[Shapes of Freedom, 3/6]
... You know, you can feel that you owned this  p e r s o n a l i t y  a while ago, when you weren’t conscious about it, when unnatural behavioral reflexes weren’t yet tightly wired through your basal ganglia. At that time, you were happy to just... be. You still remember the thrill of its sensations, the truth of its signals, the accuracy of its unadulterated instinct. But it’s all foggy now. Intangible. 
Maybe that’s precisely the point of all this. Maybe your destiny lays onto dissipating that fog. Maybe this action will bring you to another life dimension with a different (better?) perception of the world, lead you to something more fulfilling, more  r i g h t  that you’d only find by moving your a** towards to follow that never failing creative instinct of yours...
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
Irgendwie haben wir es geschafft, den Tag zu überstehen.  sherlockalbus zahnt und durchlebt gerade einen Schub. Den ganzen Tag waren Handwerker bei uns. Statt geplant vier Stunden schufteten die Jungs achteinhalb Stunden durch. Ich war dankbar, dass sie vorankamen, sie waren dankbar, dass ich sie nicht rausschmiss, sondern all meine Termine und Pläne vertagte. Doch jedes Mal wenn ich das Baby schlafen legte, ertönte der Schlagbohrer. Wir alle waren froh als ich um sieben zum Einkaufen und Spazieren aufbrechen konnte. Auf dem Weg zum Laden war ich gerade dabei, den Bubi in den Schlaf zu schieben und per Sprachnachricht die wichtigsten Nachrichten zu beantworten, als aus einer Gruppe reichlich angeshakerter 50 bis 60 Jähriger der Spruch kam: „Wie wohl mal die Kinder werden, wenn sie die Eltern immer nur mit dem Handy sehen“ Ich rief, dass mein Kind normal wird und ging meinen Weg. Doch der Spruch ließ mich nicht los. Nach dem Einkauf ging ich nochmal zu der Gruppe und wies sie darauf hin, dass wir in niemandes Schuhe den ganzen Tag unterwegs sind, dass Mütter auch Menschen mit Beruf, Verpflichtungen und sozialen Kontakten sind, dass manche Sachen nun mal erledigt werden müssen und dass man sich kein Urteil erlauben sollten. Ich war stolz als ich ging und  sherlockalbus schlief endlich seelenruhig in seinem Wagen 
____________________________________

Reposted from @ogo.eco -   Плоггинг или  plogging - это родившееся в Швеции явление, гибрид здорового образа жизни и бережного отношения к природе. Назван он так, потому что образован от глагола “подобрать” (по-шведски “плока апп”) и существительного “джоггинг” (это, в свою очередь, медленный бег трусцой). Пробежки с мусором становятся популярными по всему миру.

Ни меня, ни и моего супруга @orlovgorskijsergey бегунами не назовёшь. Но свою модификацию плоггинга он всё же придумал, скрестив сбор мусора с собачьей прогулкой.

Многие жалуются на собачников. Встречаются даже агрессивные экошеймеры: «А о чём вы думали, когда заводили домашнее животное?! Конечно, и коты и собаки – сплошной экологический ущерб!».
К счастью, в нашем дворе любят и моего мужа, и нашу собаку.

Просто мы стараемся придерживаться правила:
место после тебя должно быть лучше, чем до тебя.

I started wondering how everyone would treat him, and me in return, for him not believing anymore. I had seen how Mormons treated other family members who didn't believe anymore. It was like they were shunned, second class, not worth talking about. They just sort of disappeared. No one asked them why they left. No one asked if they needed any help. It was horrible. It's like Mormons say (though they would never admit this), that they can be friends and care about you, but only if you're Mormon. ***Side note - I saw a member say that once in a fb group - that she wouldn't go looking for friends who weren't Mormon. 🤦‍♀️😑 As I started thinking about this more and more I realized I didn't like the Mormon culture. In fact I hated it. I was surprised at how much hate I had towards it.

Mormons judge you if you're not wearing your garments. They judge you if you're not able to go into the temple. They judge you if you exercise without garments, wear revealing clothing when on vacation or going to a dance. They judge you if you don't go on a mission.

Somehow you're ALWAYS second best if you're not measuring up to their impossible standards. It's a shaming, judgemental nightmare.

text:
We all know THAT person. ⁣
⁣
You know, the one who constantly tries to change your mind about something that’s important to them by making you feel bad about your personal life choices. ⁣
⁣
Yeah, you know the one. And chances are, you and I have probably to some degree been that person at some point in the past as well. ⁣😆
⁣
There are so many people out there trying to be “influencers,” but what does that even mean?⁣ 🤔 ⁣ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Let me tell you something. ⁣
⁣
Being a true influencer doesn’t mean shaming people for what they believe. It doesn’t mean pointing out everything wrong with others’ belief systems. It doesn’t mean being self righteous. ⁣
⁣
There are a lot of people claiming to be influencers online right now just because they have thousands of followers and likes on their posts. ⁣
⁣
To me, those are simply vanity metrics. True influence comes from the people who believe in their core what they are standing up for, who ⁣they are helping and they share their ideas, gifts and offerings with love and no judgement. ⁣ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⁣It means showing up from a space of love, encouragement and creating an environment where others can believe in themselves. ⁣
⁣
If you want to influence others, do it from your heart without shame. This is how you make a true impact.

text:
“Final lap of this pregnancy and I feel strong, excited, nervous and powerful. Mixed emotions in so much grace.” Earlier, Sameera Reddy posted, “I embrace my curves, my cheeks, my water retention and my pregnant belly with a smile.” A couple of weeks ago, in response to trolls, @reddysameera  posted a beautiful picture of herself in beachwear with the caption, “Her soul was too deep to explore by those who always swam in the shallow end. This is my answer to anyone who feels uncomfortable with me enjoying my pregnant belly.” Sameera Reddy had been trolled for her weight after her 1st pregnancy weight, and speaks up now in her second, glowing in her late pregnancy. 
Celebrity mom Sameera Reddy had been trolled for putting on a lot of weight after her first pregnancy, at a time when she was feeling low. While she admits that she had body image issues at that time, she is confident and happy during her second, and the trolls can take a hike!

A friend of mine recently gave birth. A couple of months after the delivery, she looks as trim as she did before pregnancy. At a party recently, I overheard some Indian women talking about her. “Who would even believe that she was pregnant?” they said as they considered their own belly fat and love handles. I felt sad that they felt the need to make that comparison, but I was not surprised. Aren’t such conversations all too common in India, where a woman’s body is constantly looked at, judged and talked about? 
No wonder that women feel ashamed of and unhappy about their bodies –bodies that have survived bringing brand new, beautiful human beings onto this planet; bodies that they should be proud of.

A glowing  SameeraReddy celebrating her second pregnancy
Which is why the positivity that emanates from Sameera Reddy’s social media posts about her pregnancy is refreshing. She is glowing, and why not? The actress is pregnant with her second child, and she has been sharing the most gorgeous pictures of her baby bump, and she has been open and honest about her thoughts and feelings about the same.

Read more, link in bio

text:
חוגגים 15 שנים לעמותת מצמיחים!!!!! 70,000 ילדים ובני נוער עד היום ואלפי מחנכות, יועצות, מנהלות, סטודנטים לחינוך וצוותים חינוכיים, ובעיקר 15 שנים של שיטה ייחודית שעובדת, שמצליחה, שהוכחה מחקרית, נבדקת מידי שנה וממשיכה להתפתח. 
תודה לכל המחנכות שפתחו את דלת כיתתן ונתנו בנו אמון. 
תודה לכל התלמידים המקסימים בכל הארץ ובכל המגזרים, שפתחו את ליבם, הביאו מאמץ ואומץ להפוך את כיתתם למקום מצמיח.

תודה לשותפים, קרנות וחברות עסקיות שליוו אותנו לאורך השנים ועד היום, ביניהם: שטרן זינגר, קרן משפחת ליאון, קרן DM, דן וגלוריה שוסטרמן, שגרירות ארה"ב, שותפות שיקאגו ועוד שותפים יקרים לדרך שהאמינו בנו ואפשרו לנו להגיע לעוד ועוד בתי ספר.

תודה לוועד המנהל היקר שלנו שמלווה אותנו במסירות וליו"ר הועד עדי ויגודצקי.

text:
Whether it is about how we look, what community we belong to, our lifestyle choices – we’ve been told that we are not good enough. 
When we’re constantly told, we often believe. We tell ourselves that we really aren’t good enough to fit in or that we can’t pull off what we’re set to do. But tell me, is this who you were supposed to be? Does that tag really define you? Is it what makes you who you are?

Meet a boy who suffered from anorexia and found inspiration in Spiderman, a girl who found her voice amidst the everyday crass chatter, a Muslim rapper who broke through the stereotype of his community and a rebel artist who bared her soul to her art.

Here it is – a series of conversations which bring to the table a much needed discussion. It also tells us volumes of how we see people and immediately, even without a second thought, often judge them, unknowingly. 
It’s important we talk about this, call it out in the open and rip it from it’s very roots, because otherwise, we’ll always believe that we’re not good enough.

text: Found: November 23rd, 2018 - Found q few hours after my previous post.

Today something sad happened that I decided to put into words. My parents finally moved back to Germany and I am as much happy they are back, as I am afraid of old habits and unpleasant moments. Today, two days after they’ve been back, we decided to go for a swim. I hate going to swim or be by the lake since I was younger, one of the reason being that no matter what age, I’ve always been told that i should lose weight or simply “you don’t look good”. To be clear, I was not afraid it “could” happen, it simple always did. .
When I started living alone in Berlin I realized that I started to like myself. Now, weighing +20kg, even more. I used to think it was me becoming strong on my own, also because after several years I’ve found a partner that loves me the way I am 🖤 and all that is true, but I also came to realize that most of it came from being literary apart from the comments and pain that make me feel that way to beginn with. .
Today we wanted to swim and after long inner thought, especially the fear of comments from my mom, I decided to not care and simply join. When I finally had my swimsuit on, my mother looked at me and says “you look horrible, especially your hair”. Silence. I turned around and said I won’t join, and she simply replied with okay, bye.

I don’t care if a stranger thinks my legs are big or my head is too bald. But I do care if love ones do. It makes me wonder what’s going through their mind. Do they think this won’t hurt, or that it should?
I know I am a strong person, capable of loving myself, able to not care what others say, but I am disappointed, exhausted and deeply sad to be told to not be allowed to like myself the way I am. To not define beauty the way I want to or at least to let me be, especially when it’s so hot outside. 
In the end I stayed home in pain and decided to create this instead. I feel better now. There is so much more to tell and I will sometime, in hopes to make others feel less alone with issues like these ♥️ .
.
.
.

 tessholiday

text:
Something I've learned lately.
Quite simple but with  profound implications.

I grew up  privileged and didn't really need to have a job. Honestly I can't say that was the best for my spiritual and practical development. I always got to do what I wanted and as an entrepreneur I did many things. But when I tried to learn the  discipline it would take to do things I didn't want to do, or take my work to the next level, I failed myself over and over. I had gotten used to  shaming myself for not being able to get everything done. There was something wrong with me, why wasn't I able to do more with my  privilege? Why wasn't I living up to my  potential?

I finally realized....how in the heck I was I supposed to learn to do this for myself when I had never really had to be  accountable to anyone else?
So, I stopped shaming myself for needing  accountability, and realized that most everybody does.  Discipline is not easy for many of us.
Especially Someone like me who has multiple interests and  talents, and what I like to call  creative ADD. 😂

I Knew I needed to learn to work and be in a schedule. So I got a full-time  job for the first time ever and I'm learning that now...in my 40s. 
Things have turned around quickly In a relatively short time. 
It's never too late to  reinvent yourself and do work that fulfills you.

New post! -  https://kellybwarner.com/2018/10/25/a-gift-from-the-universe/

A gift from the universe - “'Shame is a controlling device. Shaming someone is an attempt to prevent the person from behaving in a way that embarrasses us'... ...But today she was grabby, even the baby was protesting. I asked for space, she followed me into my room. So I got angry, and she got sad. This is our routine with disagreements. And when I talk to her, I talk about how important it is to not hurt other people, they’ll feel upset or angry. Why do I do it this way? Because my belief is that it’s ineffective when I say I am hurt or angry based on how she’s responded in the past. So I instead use this version. I use shame. “If you keep doing it, others won’t like you.

And, I use this tactic often. It stops the behavior. But, by full admittance, only for a short moment. As parents, sometimes we just need that moment. We live moment to moment. And then, I in turn, shame myself for how I parent in this moments. I carry the weight of all of these mistakes and use them against myself all too often."  juliecameron

text:
Book Review: Jon Ronson - ‘So You’ve Been Publicly Shamed'

A recurring theme in my reading after tackling The Scarlet Letter last year, this is my first Ronson book and probably won’t be my last. Though his blurring between serious journalistic enquiry and Vice-tier all-about-the-author-core can be frustrating, it’s an enjoyable read and brings to light an issue I think many of us need to think about more. If anything, the biggest takeaway has been that my avoidance of twitter is definitely the right call, and I now will avoid that hole like the plague, as it almost seems to congregate all the character traits I dislike the most in people.

Ronson has a generally interesting fascination in the interactions of people that I share, and presents his ideas in an easy to digest manner, but his desire to be impartial leaves the book without much of a conclusion. It’s really just a series of observations, and in a way that makes it better - he allows us to make up our own minds. A good read, and I’m glad I picked it up because it is hotly relevant to some of my own work. I’ve had Ronson’s The Psychopath Test recommended to me now and I’m sure I’ll get to that soon enough.

Year: 2015
Publisher: Pan Macmillan
Genres: non-fiction, pop sociology
Read from: 5th May-20th June 2019

Up next: replacing this as my non-fiction reading will be “Coming Back to Me” by Marcus Trescothick

text:
Короче, смотри и продолжай смотреть все лучшее в Черном зеркале — "Враг народа", завершивший третий сезон сериала.
⠀
Раз уж зашла речь о Келли Макдональд, то почему бы не посмотреть серию с ее участием? Во-первых, все показанное уже начинает сбываться (да-да, пчелы уже умирают), а неудачный пост в соцсетях наверняка приведет к катастрофе шейминга. Во-вторых, серия удивительно красиво снята. Ну то есть, это снова Англия, а когда Англия не была красивой? Вот и мы считаем преступлением пропускать мимо своего внимания подобного рода эстетику. Боже, храни Королеву, ее земли и вообще все, что связано с Великобританией. Есть, конечно, в серии моменты, вызывающие некоторые вопросы, но — камон! — это же Черное Зеркало, здесь и должно быть противоречие на противоречии. Да и потом, в сравнении с пятым сезоном...
⠀
Вообще, конкретно этот сюжет заставляет задуматься о вреде социальных сетей не с позиции бабушек из соседнего подъезда, а-ля "что за молодежь пошла, в своих интернетах шастают, нелюди!!!", а скорее, с позиции современного человека, который пользуется ими. Вот смотришь и думаешь: какую бы мысль ты ни сказал, обязательно найдутся люди, которые высмеять захотят или, того хуже, заклеймить. И уже вопрос" А нужны ли нам эти социальные сети?" становится не просто филослфским, а вроде даже вечным, по типу "В чем смысл жизни?" Словом, как и большинство эпизодов, эта серия заставляет о многом порассуждать, но в итоге — спойлер! — все опять сведется к неоднозначночти. Или к ответу, озвучив который, можно стать врагом народа, но это так, всего-то дружеское напоминание :) ⠀
Серии мы ставим 8 подозрительных тортиков с угрозами из 10 и рекомендуем к просмотру
⠀

text:
THOUGHTS ARE NOT TRUTH - mindfulness is always important but I think it’s most important when it comes to the process of turning our thoughts into our words and express ourselves. —
As l wrote the other day “what happens to a thought when you don’t think it”, remember the nugget l took away from the meditation?, and this is in the same line. 
A thought is not you. 
Its not even an expression of you.
A thought is just a thought. —
But that does not mean that a thought does not shape you, because it does! 
And if you express a thought that is not aligned with your souls purpose you are on a discourse that might end up being really difficult to stear back home from. 
If you turn a thought into speech that is not truly an expression of you, those words have now affected others and their perception of you. They will now meet you with the foundation of your words and not who you really are.
This is where bridges are burned.
This is where wars are started.
—
So what to do?
Well, we end up where l always end up.
If you have thoughts that are not compassionate and out of loving kindness they are not truth. 
At all!
They are a blip. 
They are expressions of fear, anger, guilt or shame and they are using diversions as blaming, shaming and complaining.
They are not you.

They have gifts to you because you can find out where they come from, why you think they are true, but please dont make them true. 
Remember; “what happens to a thought when you dont think it”… Let go of it.. Meditate on it

Get back to compassion and loving kindness and find yourself there. … and then speak…

text:
WHAT IS MELANIN? .
.
.
Melanin is a pigment that is produced by cells known as melanocytes in the skin of most animals, including humans. This pigment comes in different shades, depending on the genetic makeup of the individual. ... Individuals, who are exposed to UV light, such as the sun, will produce more melanin for protection.
.
.
. 
Everyone has about the same number of cells that make melanin, but not everybody makes the same amount of melanin. Some people make more melanin than others, the more melanin your skin makes, the darker your skin is. .
.

text:
momshaming and  parentshaming is a big problem. It effects the parents ability to parent appropriately and therefore can be detrimental to their child(ren)

I’ve had my fair share of being mom shamed. I’ve had an older lady make a nasty comment about how she didn’t know which was more annoying my older sons obnoxious singing or my youngest crying. Granted they were both being really loud and I was trying my best to get them under control but that was not helpful for her to say that. It stressed me out and hindered my ability to parent my children

On the other side of the coin there is  momguilt which is just self-shaming. I’m sure we all have felt this at some point or another because we didn’t feel up to par in our parenting. But you need to remind yourself and each other that we are doing an AMAZING job! Parenting is tough and we don’t need to shame each other nor ourselves. It’s important that we have confidence in our parenting skills and shaming strips us of that confidence

I talk about another one of my experiences with mom shame as well as why it’s so detrimental in my New “Sweet”  blogpost link in profile. 
Have you ever been mom shamed?

text:
So I’m working with the idea of  shame and  guilt as vicarious emotional currencies, meaning energies we can tap and use to get the natural beneficiaries of violence (the partners, the adult children, the generations removed descendants of colonial invaders or murderous police lieutenants) to provide financial  reparations to survivors of violence. 
Now I’m thinking about it from the lens of my life. My former partner is a sexual predator. His company, Google, is protecting him and has refused to return my hacked documents that implicate him in rape by fraud and proxy. 
Hiring a lawyer isn’t an option. I’ve had three, and the whole experience was a farce of justice. Plus, after years of hacks and stints in safe houses, the case is now federal, and I live in the world’s oldest colony,  Borikén, and work for  PrisonAbolition. 
Complications.  ComplexTrauma too! That’s just basic context. 
So, about  PublicShaming as a vicarious emotional currency. Do I name him — and the members of his family? He’s the child of two PhD’s while I’m the only child of a single mother who raised me on welfare and a missing father often homeless or incarcerated. Do I name his siblings, his colleagues, his friends? 
What happens when shame is mobilized,  monetized, and marketed by survivors — me and  MeToo? I get chills at the thought. 
I mean, in a sense I’m engaging in public  shaming by writing these comments. But shame isn’t financial security for someone who has survived structural violence and still struggles with it. It certainly doesn’t alleviate my concern for other victims. It doesn’t much change the digital landscape. Or does it?  NiUnaMenos. 
And what about  compassion, and  forgiveness? What about  grace and  mercy? Or  RadicalSelfLove? Speaking of which, I need a  cocktail I’m so stressed over these queries.

Another woman told me emphatically that I wasn't that pretty. She went into detail about brown eyes vs blue, etc.

Why? Women, can we call each other beautiful? This is me after my tearful reaction to her words.

I may not fit into society's conditioned standards of conventional beauty. If we lived in ancient Mayan times our standards of beauty would be flat, sloped foreheads, and big noses.

Whether we fit into a standard or not, can we at least be kind to one another--and ourselves? Can we recognize each of our unique beauty out of society's perspective of perfection?

text:
•Body shaming, read below•

The media fuels body shaming, it occurs daily under categories completely unrelated to diet like ‘celebrity gossip’ or so called ‘journalism’. What makes body shaming readable material is beyond me. 
The media grasp at anything for financial success and higher ratings; they catch the latest celebrity bloated and suddenly its pregnancy news, what dignity do they have?

We absorb this. Young children absorb this. They including ourselves begin to view this behaviour as a norm and as expected. And that’s when we compare.

Subconsciously or consciously we objectify ourselves and put ourselves through scrutiny just to fit that ‘mould’ the media has repeatedly taught us. 
What frustrates me is that people don’t eat the same. By ignoring that slice of cake your dying for or you miss meals because you don’t see yourself as beautiful. And it stresses me because we all have beauty and we should have the freedom to eat what we want to, as long as it’s not damaging your health.

The media has possessed our younger selves that the only way we can be pretty is to be incredibly skinny.

I think we should have the choice to decide for ourselves what is gorgeous about our bodies. Its not a choice for the media, or anyone else for that matter. 
As always, Bridgey x

[Shapes of Freedom, 1/6]
“Be yourself!” is surely one of the most popular advices of our time. But when these words first fly into your brain — like a Prince Charming’s kiss tearing you out of everything that has been told to Little-you during your many years of out-of-love-but-somehow-manipulative education — you get lost. 
Because you don’t know who the hell you’re supposed to be. Because you believe you won’t make any friends, or worse lose the only one or two you’ve got, if you allow your true self to be. Because you are used to feel  a s h a m e d  of who you are, of the way you speak, look, laugh. Because there was always some people who — out of love — were spying on every single one of your movements and each detail of your actions to make you feel the shame that they actually do themselves.
.
.
.
Photo @xiomarabenderphotographer
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
Bella Thorne Rips Whoopi Goldberg For Shaming Nude Photos on ‘The View’

 Whoopi
Bella Thorne 'Shame On You, Whoopi!!!' For Shaming My Nude Pics 6/18/2019 3:19 PM PDT Bella Thorne is firing back at Whoopi Goldberg after she seemingly shamed Bella for having nude photos on her phone, on the cloud, or anywhere. In a series of super emotional posts Tuesday, Bella tearfully blasted Whoopi ... who took the stance on "The View" that celebs who take nude photos are just asking for trouble with hackers and, essentially, said they should know better.  Bella said Whoopi's comment only inflames a painful situation. She also suggested Whoopi's lack of sympathy toward young people who get exposed this way is part of the reason people commit suicide after their nudes are leaked. In case you missed it ... Bella's Twitter was hacked last week, and over the weekend she posted a series of topless photos in order to beat her alleged hacker to the punch. She says the person was attempting to extort her with the racy pics.  Whoopi, Meghan McCain, Sunny Hostin and Joy Behar debated the issue in Monday's episode of "The View" ... and their convo clearly triggered Bella.  Bella says she's not going on "The View" anymore, because she doesn't want to be judged by a bunch of older women ... and she's calling out the hosts for brainwashing the next generation and accusing them of some serious double standards. 💜😈 “Why?” is a question I ask myself a lot🙄Today I went to the farmer’s market feeling good, ready to raise my energy and spread joy. The first booth I went to had these awesome marigolds and an old lady behind them. During our conversation, she asked me, “how can someone that skinny be healthy?” OK. 
WHY did she feel like she should say that to me? WHY did she think it WASNT a horrible insult?? Is she saying she is worried for me??? I’m your customer. I don’t get it. 
But lady, it’s GENETICS and idk what else to tell ya. I eat normally. Why do people think that’s different from fat-shaming? There are skinny motherfuckers out there that don’t do drugs and eat fattening foods. 
Just, don’t tell people they’re “too skinny” or “need to put some meat on their bones” bc it fucking sucks when you DO eat fatty foods and exercise but you don’t gain weight. 
I am happy with my body, and i’m healthy af. Don’t try to tell me i’m too this or too that. I ain’t going around doing that in your life. 
The more people that understand this, the better I will feel inside. :-) thanks ☀️☀️☀️☀️

text:
Had to pause 30min into my run because Little Miss decided she needed her mom.  It might not be a consistent 45 min but at least I got my workout in for the day! 
I’ve debated if I want to bring this up or not...mom shaming, body shaming, jealousy, or criticism.  We all judge other people whether we admit it or not. 
Over the past 6+ weeks, after the congratulations of baby, I hear in a half joke half disgusted voice “You don’t even look like you had a baby”  A few people didn’t even think Evelyn was mine... lots of “not fairs” and “you’re already running?!?” I know for some it’s a slight compliment but it doesn’t come off that way... I won’t feel bad for working out or running or looking fairly good 9 weeks postpartum. 
Instead of judging, either work on yourself or say something nice without the condescending undertones🤷🏻‍♀️😒. I get it, we all want something we can’t/don’t have... I do it too, but I keep it to myself. 
I workout to make myself feel good, not for anyone else.  I can always count on @sweatwithstudio for lifting me up and creating a safe space for all!  It feels good to hear all the positive affirmations throughout the workouts by each and every coach!!!

text:
Vakar su drauge sėdėjom, gurkšnojom, kas kavą, kas arbatą, ir mėgavomės vasariškais desertais. O prie tų desertų aptarinėjome gėdinimo (“shaming’o) kultūrą. Kitaip tariant, kai žmogui bandoma pasakyti, kad jis nėra tinkamas toks, koks jis yra.

Tas gėdinimas dažnai prasideda žodžiais: “Iš kur Tu toks…?”. Būtent šiuo klausimu paskatiname žmogų pasijusti nepatogiai. Ne kartą mačiau, kaip man prieš akis net labai artimas žmogus ima ir pradeda muistytis. Tuomet pabertų žodžių rinkiniu ima gintis. O kai nepavyksta apsiginti, ima ir pradeda kaltinti kitus. “Aš tapau Toks, nes Kitas mane Tokiu padarė.” Prisipažinsiu ir aš tūkstantį kartų panašų sakinį pasakydavau. Ir ko tik nekaltinau dėl savo gyvenimo – tėvų, brolio, buvusių antrųjų pusių, draugų, mokytojų, dėstytojų, visuomenės, nepažįstamųjų. Kol vieną dieną pabudau ir supratau, kad kaltindama juos tik didinu savo ydas. Tą pačią dieną pradėjau mokytis suprasti, kodėl jie visi mano gyvenime atsirado. Ir supratau viena – visos tos savybės, dėl kurių atsiradimo kaltinau kitus, seniai gyveno manyje ir aplinkiniai tik jas sustiprino. Tiksliau, aš pati jas sustiprinau su savo interpretacijomis.

O kad nuslėpčiau tas ydas, dažniau ėmiau pastebėti kitų. Dėl to, tikriausia ir gėdinimo kultūra atsirado – nes gėdinant kitą bent kelias minutes yra puiki proga pabėgti nuo savo minusų. Bet deja, lengviau bus nuo gepardo pabėgti nei nuo savęs.

text:
Is it just me??? When I go to the doctor, I feel like I’m treated like a hypochondriac. The doctor is uninterested in my foot pain until I lose 50 pounds, and when I ask for help only offers strategies I can’t afford. “Walk more.” Easy to say if you don’t have foot pain! He ends the appointment by  shaming me that if I was really motivated, I could do it. Must be nice to have all the answers, access to care, and no problems.
😠
I fell 10 days ago and landed on my hands and knees. Immediately had swelling in the back of my right hand. No big deal. Iced it and rested. But the bump hasn’t gone down, and the moderate pain hasn’t subsided. Urgent care told me no fractures on day 2; it’s day ten now and it’s not really any better. But I’m doubting myself and what it will cost to go in and see a doctor again.  tiredofnotbeingseen 
Thank goodness I don’t have cancer or anything serious. I figure they’d refuse to check it till I lost 100 pounds.
 childhoodtrauma often leads to

text:
There is NO  Love in  Shaming... 💔

I was born and raised up in South Texas... my mind recalls memories of hearing older people's scorn as, "shame on you!" ...for Whatever, and to Whomever, I am unsure. I just remember that being a fairly common phraseology for chastisement down here. And it made sense, most of the time.

As an adult, I came across the works of my cousin (in Jest, for the name is the same 😜 no direct relation, that I'm aware of) Dr. Brene Brown, whose monumental Work on studying the effects of  Shame have revealed to me what a major component of relational disfunction the carrying of Shame can become... my family, the alcoholics and otherwise, were frequent users of Sarcasm as Humor. It never occurred to me that such banter could strengthen One's inner sense of Shame, until I was in my late 40's... 💔

I now feel that, while an occasional quip or pun might be fun, I have ZERo desire or intentions of participating in anything that can cause another person to feel "less than", or shameful... we are all of the same Maker. He made NO junk! (another Southern expression, y'all 😇) so I pray that anyone dealing with current or residual Shame thoughts, feelings, identity traits, or other such negative manifestations of  awaken to  theTruth!

You, (yes YOU!) are a  ChildOfGod , gloriously  created in His image. 💞 There is NO place for the carrying of any negative labels or condemnations...  awaken and  arise in  ChristConsciousness awareness, that YOU are a son or daughter of the King of kings, and that YOU were made for a very special and unique  Purpose! It wasn't to waste away your life in alcoholic delusions, or depressive anxiety and  Worry... you have a unique and special kinda Love within you. It will awaken through focused  prayer and  Understanding of God's Law... 💞

Love Him. Love Self. Love Neighbors... May His greatest Blessings of Love, Grace, Mercy, and Peace leave you filled with Awe and Wonder, replacing all shame, guilt, and Anger, for those are the Lies (and favorite Tools) of the

text:
This has been eating away at me a little bit because of snide/underhanded comments and today something kinda broke it all. Don’t get me wrong I find it hilarious that people still do this stuff and still some have highschool mentality. 
But, my weight is my concern and potentially my Dr. It doesn’t effect anyone else so I don’t feel like anyone else has a need to comment on it. Especially if you don’t know me and don’t know if I am actively trying to lose weight or not. 
If this was a few years ago, this would have worn away at me until I broke down but today I’m glad that I can see the funny side in how pathetic it is for people to do this. The only reason I’m writing this is because even though I see the funny side, it doesn’t stop it getting to me occasionally. Especially because it’s not just kids, kids I could deal with but it’s adults and people older than me. There’s no need for it

No  shaming here.,,.just pragmatic objectivity.

I would like to ask you all a simple question...On a daily basis how many times do you tend to shame other women. Answers!? Well I don’t think it is even countable in numbers. The amount to which a woman holds prejudice and bias against another women is a pity and to know that instead of being each other’s pillars we are the wrecking balls who tirelessly strive to knock each other’s walls down is nothing but utterly shameful! I have faults, you have faults, WE ALL HAVE FAULTS then why instead of accepting each other for these mistakes and trying to improve them we sabotage other people’s images. I mean, if we can’t take a stand for a fellow woman how do we expect women to survive in this patriarchal society where men treat us just with the same sick mentality as our own kind does. IT IS IMPORTANT FOR US TO UNDERSTAND THAT UNITED WE STAND DIVIDED WE FALL!!! If today we promise ourselves to take a stand for every female who has fallen a prey to all the shaming and ignominy then together we can heal eachother and grow those pillars again on which the foundation of sisterhood lies!!! text:
When you are sharing your opinion, explaining your position, outlining why you did what you did, can you do so without attacking the other person? 
What is “attacking” communication? Blaming. Shaming. Criticizing.  Trying to put yourself in a position of “one up” and the person “one down.” Minimizing their feelings or opinion. 
If you feel the need to attack someone to prove your point or to be heard, then that is an opportunity to check in with yourself and ask what is going on with me that I feel so threatened here... why am I seeing a tiger when there isn’t one around? Remind yourself that your thoughts and feelings are valid, you do not have to shout to be heard, and making someone small does not make you big. 💜

text:
In South Asian culture, women are often made to "sit out" in the corner of a home and remain untouched during their periods. We're prevented from going to mosques and temples, and shamed for a natural part of life. The three of us grew up in Hindu homes with very different expectations during our time of the month. In this episode, we're going to explore why we aren't allowed to do those things, rant a little about how we aren't dirty or impure because we're on our period, and talk about how a biological process that is empowering and allows us to bring a life into the world has been shamed, hidden and awkwardly approached in South Asian culture, and how Western and Eastern menstrual equity are very, very different concepts. The new episode of  TWD is out! We're looking forward to hearing what you have to say.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text: Currently watching my little one pick her boogers... And don't worry she approved me posting this photo 😂🤣... So... Sadly I'm listening to this woman chase her 3-4 year old around the pool with sunscreen. She's telling her child " no one is whiter than ypu, you need sunscreen, you are very white, let mommy put sunscreen on your white skin, you're the whitest kid at the pool" she's been repeating this to her child for a good 3 minutes now as the kid giggles and runs away.  Maybe I'm more sensitive to her wording because my daughter is mixed... But... My thought process is... You're going to give your child a complex... She is forever going to feel like she is not normal...not like the rest of the world.... Or.... You're going to make her love being so white that she's going to be a brat to anyone with different color skin... I understand the mother's point... The child has little melatonin so she's going to burn easily.... But explaining to her child that she will be hurt and burnt by the sun would be a more age appropriate response to get your kid to wear sunscreen... They don't know wtf being white means... They don't know that they can get cancer and or that in 2 hours their skin will be so red and in pain .... Using the word white over and over and over ..... Is going to give this poor kid some body image issues or racist issues.  Maybe I'm looking to deeply into this.... But... Ages 1-8 make or break a kid .. they are sponges!! Explaining things in age appropriate ways is important to not create adult monsters. 😏 This is my 3rd go around I've learned to watch how I speak to my children. Our words create who our kids become.   whitekid 🙄  judging 🤚

text:
When I put up a Facebook status for this feature, Parthiv reached out to me in my inbox. 
He told me how he was always judged and made fun of for being skinny. He felt if he told his story, it could help people who were facing similar issues, and I couldn’t have agreed more. ° ° °

One of the things that Parthiv said mirrored my ideas and why I started this feature in the first place. He said “Being skinny or fat is not a crime. It is subjective. Everyone has an opinion and you will find people who will comment or bully you everywhere. There is no escaping it. It can get really tough especially when these people are your relatives and give you unsolicited advice that will make no sense.” The trick according to him is to accept yourself. “You were born fabulous” he exclaims. ° ° °

text: If you try to make someone do something, you will crush them with expectations. Not even God does that. People need to decide for themselves what to do, without coercion or shaming or manipulation, or else they’re only doing it to get you quiet. They won’t ever know why, and it will never become a part of them. Making demands is an external apparatus that will chokehold the people you claim to love. But if you truly love them, by listening and investing and sharing and even liking them, this is the only sort of love that will tenderize a heart to seek better for itself. To shame is to lay down bricks to make a shape, but without a soul. To show grace will take longer, but it’s to plant a seed that pushes through the dirt into the air, towards a life that can breathe on its own. This is true empowerment.

Instead of forcing change through shaming or demanding, let the person know your boundaries. “In order to protect my peace and sanity, if you continue to do x that hurts me profoundly without changing then I will have to remove myself from this relationship/situation.” Grace is so important, but grace without boundaries will get you hurt over and over. Demands don’t work, but letting people know your boundaries and that they cannot expect you to just take being hurt over and over gracefully works.

text:
Yes,  Pride is now a celebration. A  celebration that grew from a  riot. A riot that grew from years of  anguish, fear, secrecy,  shaming, and eventually  resistance. Years of solitude and familial  abandonment, of arrests and police brutality, of bigotry and  hatecrimes... sound familiar? True, in so many ways we are not so evolved. In many communities globally it is still illegal to exist in one’s queerness. Folks can still be fired from their careers for loving their partner. Or worse, “arrested” and then disappeared. Today. This is still happening today. 
So while Pride is a celebration of the liberties many of us are fortunate to now enjoy, let us be mindful. Let us remember that if some of us are not free, none of us are free. Let us remember that these freedoms we have in  California can vanish tomorrow, and are not consistently true in these “United” States. [not to mention the ugly that still exists even in this left-coast state despite our progressive efforts]
Let us remember that the patriarchal, heteronormative,  capitalists seek to gain in vain - pushing their  rainbow swag to fool you into believing they support  LGBTQ+ issues. Do your  research before spending your  vote on how we continue forward. Better yet, spend your money on supporting  QTPOC owned businesses,  entrepreneurs, etc! Let our choices remind our communities that we  support each other and that we’re here alllll year long, not just in June during  pridemonth. Let our choices bridge the months between Black History month, Pride month, and Latin@ heritage month (among other holidays) to speak to the  intersections of our  identities not being pigeonholed. So yes, let us stand  proud, today and every day, and let us truly  honor those on who’s shoulders we stand. ••• Swipe to see a few of my favorite  qtpoc folks doing amazing work, give ‘em a follow, support their work, cheer them on! :)

text: Found: August 2018 - The baby department. Wasteland of Cups.

Recently, my father (a covert narcissist) singled me out in front of my entire family in an attempt to shame me. He angrily said “why do you always say ‘no’????!!!” I thought, « hmmm, maybe because your  demands are always inconsiderate »🤔 But instead of justifying myself, I took a deep breath, scanned the room, and cheerfully retorted “oh, thank you!!! I  have been working on setting boundaries”
In that moment, I understood that my boundaries were well  set, and effectively working.
⚡️what was meant as a criticism turned out to be a compliment ⚡️😂

So You’ve Been Publicly Shamed
⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
Jon Ronson’s exploration of public shaming in the modern day is a really important and fascinating read. Studying real life examples of how people’s lives have been ruined by everyday mistakes and delving into the history and reason behind public shaming definitely makes you stop and think. For me the success of a good non-fiction lies in its ability to make the reader consider different viewpoints and deliver otherwise forgotten sides of the story. I’d highly recommend this as well as any of his other works, including The Psychopath Test.

I go to the gym because my body is ugly ⤐  shame
I go to the gym because it helps me feel good ⤐  honor
I’m not eating cookies, sugar, or sweets, because I’m a fat slob ⤐  shame
I’m not eating cookies, sugar, or sweets because I choose to put healthy food in my body as fuel ⤐ honor
He deserves to be in the dog house for what he did to you ⤐ shame
I acknowledge what he did, but do you understand why he did that? ⤐  honor
I fucked up and smoked a cigarette, i’m too weak to quit ⤐ shame
I fucked up and smoked I cigarette, but i’m not giving up on myself ⤐ honor

Shame perpetuates more shame and unhelpful cycles. Shame doesn’t lay a solid foundation of forgiveness and continued effort; honor and respect do.

Where have you been trying to motivate yourself or maybe someone else by utilizing shame as the means? Can you reframe that into a more honoring and empowering way of motivation?

I pressured myself the most despite attaining and breaking so many  barriers...and all because of the pressure from  society. Fuck what they say just stay focused.  Women stop  shaming eachother please and thanks! From my journey to yours 🌹.

text:
EID MUBARAK!
JANGAN JADIKAN LEBARAN JADI MOMEN MENYEBALKAN.
.
.
True story, baru saja aku alami hari ini.
Langsung kutulis karena aku kesal setengah mati. .
.
🍁🍁🍁
.
.
X : "Loh, kamu hamil?" (Ngomentarin badanku. Body shaming)
.
.
.
Me : "Nggak." (Langsung pasang muka masam biar yang ngomong ngerasa kalau aku nggak suka)
.
.
.
X : "Lah, serius nggak hamil? Kok kayak hamil?" (Malah ngelunjak. Seharusnya ketika aku jawab nggak, ya udah stop di situ. Bukan malah maido kalau kata orang Jawa).
.
.
.
Me : (Diem aja dan keluar rumah tanpa ngerespon, berharap si X ngerasa).
.
.
.
X : (Dari dalam sedikit teriak, mungkin biar kedengaran ) "Si Y udah isi lagi loh. Udah mau 3 anaknya." .
.
🍁🍁🍁
.
.
Allahu Akbar!
.
.
.
Wallahi.
Nyesel nyamperin buat say hi. 
Niat silaturahmi, menemui saudara yang sudah lama tak dijumpai, berujung sakit hati seperti ini. .
.
.
Apa memang kepekaan masyarakat kita itu 0 BESAR sehingga shaming begini jadi kebiasaan? .
.
.
Mau si Y punya anak 12 juga bodo amat. Bukan urusanku dan nggak ngaruh buat aku. .
.
.
Punya anak itu BUKAN PERLOMBAAN. Jumlah anak yang sudah banyak juga bukanlah sebuah PENCAPAIAN. Si Y isi lagi dan anaknya hampir 3 juga nggak bikin dia lebih baik dari aku atau dari orang lainnya :) .
.
.
So, guys, jaga mulutnya ya. 
Jangan sampai lebaran mendadak berubah jadi momen menyebalkan. .
.
.
Mentang-mentang setan nanti sudah dilepaskan, jangan dijadikan justifikasi kalau kamu boleh ngomong shaming sembarangan. .
.
.
Jangan pula komentar "mbok jadi orang jangan baperan" karena yang seharusnya berubah adalah kamu yang tidak bisa mengendalikan lisan. .
.
.
Ingat. 
Kadang manusia memang lebih setan dari pada setan.
Jangan sampai kita jadi salah satunya karena ketidakmampuan kita menjaga lisan :)
.
.
.
🍁🍁🍁
.
.
.
MOHON MAAF LAHIR BATIN YA.
Terimakasih sudah menjadi penikmat setia tulisan-tulisan dan postingan di akun ini. Ambil yang baik, tinggalkan yang buruk ya 🤗
.
.
.
YUK, KITA JAGA LISAN KITA AGAR MOMEN LEBARAN TIDAK BERUBAH JADI MOMEN MENYEBALKAN ❤
.
.
.

text:
This is actually for both women and men however, it's a general question I have for the women who read this.  Have you dealt with it on Twitch, Mixer, Instagram, or any social media and how did you deal with it?  It's a real problem that we women have to deal with on a daily basis in some cases. If you've experienced this, and have advice, please share.  I know there are women out there that have, but don't know how to react. They feel embarrassed or don't know how to ask for help. I hope this reaches someone that needs help.  Never blame yourself or take anything they say to heart. You are beautiful and always be YOU no matter what anyone says.  Fuck disgusting mean people.  They're the ones with issues.
I'm posting because I had this issue on Saturday night.  I instantly ban them, give them no attention whatsoever. I feel they want that, they want the reaction, and I give them nothing.  I'm not a person who likes conflict, drama, or negativity.  I'd like to consider myself one of nicest people you'll ever meet. I don't deal well with people saying mean hurtful things, and I don't know what to do at times. I know they're are others out there like me.  So if you have advice or personal experience you'd like to share or just need to vent, please do.  We woman have to stick together! Let's help each other. ✌💜🤗

text:
No one taught me what to do with my feelings as a  highlysensitivechild : how to manage and regulate my emotional states exacerbated by living in a chaotic unpredictable home. I’m pretty sure I’m still learning how to do it. 😂
.
In fact my childhood was rife with mixed messages and a great deal of  minimizing and  shaming. .
.
I suppose it’s no surprise that my turning-5-on-Tuesday ! boy is incredibly sensitive, extremely creative and theatrical and exceedingly intense. I repeat, not mellow. Emotionally that is. Parenting him, it’s demanding to understate it. He’s also incredibly cuddly, very funny, and highly bright and imaginative. Oh and strong. So Stroong.
.
We made these charts this morning in a bit of a rush when I realized how long overdue it is to have a visual, concrete conversation about what to do when we’re furious and deeply upset. .
.
I realized I hadn’t been giving him clear enough guidance and protocols for how to self-regulate. He gets just apoplectic when clothes aren’t right, sleeves don’t match in length or basically whenever he doesn’t get his way. He screams so loudly I worry a neighbor will call the cops 😂😭 flails, hits, kicks (just Chris and me, he’s a angel with everyone else) and just has nuclear meltdowns on the reg. I have to make sure he’s not  hangry too and give him enough fat and protein.
.
I don’t do well with this behavior as a survivor of childhood abuse. I lose it more often than I’d like. Screaming and hitting are a huge trigger. Oof.  gettingtriggeredbyourchildren how is that not a hashtag? .
.
As a parents  of little ones we are charged with regulating ourselves AND our kids. Thank goodness I grew up with  emotionalliteracy 
Ideally we as parents model healthy coping skills. (As opposed to a lot of cursing under our breath and emotional eating)
How gratifying to watch him show chris and his friend how to  crocodilebreath and  windbreath  Some of these tools I made up, some are based on what I’ve learned about the nervous system and some I’ve collected from others. 🙏🏽
.

Wie fühlt sich emotionaler Hunger an?

Emotionaler Hunger, Seelenhunger oder wie auch immer Du den Drang nach Essen ohne eindeutige körperliche Hungersignale nennen magst, kommt meist plötzlich. 
Dieser steigt schnell und vehement an, Du verspürst Unruhe, Nervösität, Hibbligkeit, Gereiztheit etc. wenn Du versuchst, ihn zu ignorieren.

Wichtig ist: der emotionale Hunger ist kaum/schwer aushaltbar.

text:
My reaction whenever someone tells me to “Go eat something!” or “Put some meat on those bones!” ⬇️⬇️
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
Being different does not mean being less than. I would never think to suggest that a full-figured person cut back on their food intake, so understand why I take offense when people find it acceptable to spout off these things regarding my body. The implication that in order to be thin you must be starving and suffering is a twisted and harmful way of thinking.  Real women know their worth, no matter what size they are. They eat cheeseburgers, they work out, they are naturally slim, they are voluptuous, they are plus-size and they LOVE themselves. They have integrity, they are strong, they are kind and they never make snide comments about the body type of another woman. Maybe one day I’ll dive deeper into my personal experience with this topic. But for now please understand what your words mean and the value they hold. I’m confident in who I am and the body I was born with and work daily to maintain, but so many young girls these days aren’t. Let’s work together to destroy the lies about  beingskinny and  bodyshaming 🙌🏻 @katiebinghamsmith

text: I recently saw a post by one of my mentors about the Body Acceptance Challenge that really hit home with me. So often when im around friends i feel uncomfortable by their comments towards me about my body or what I eat. "Jordan eat a burger will ya." We need to accept all body types. Skinny, heart shaped, freckled, big boobed, etc. Every body is different. I work hard to feel comfortable to be in this skin. To have a healthy body so that i can chase my boys around. Dont shame those who are doing the same. Lets praise those who are putting in the work to be the best versions of themselves. Were all the same at the heart of it. We all have rolls when we sit down. We all have cellulite. We all have that one body part that we scrutinize more than any other body part. Lets change how we talk to each other and lift each other up. Our bodies are beautiful things that can do amazing things and they come in all shapes and sizes.

text:
GUNDU KATTU SIRRIKI

It is not necessary for you to have a picture perfect face or body to be infront of the camera! You just have to be YOU, be CONFIDENT, be DAUNTLESS!! I am pretty sure that everyone is facing body shaming nowadays! So this what I pretty hear almost everytime! " hey, you put on weight dy la" ;"your face so chubby dy" "your thighs are so big, dont wear shorts" !! I am so done with all these statements or comments towards my body size or shape! Okay I was thin and I put on weight !! Its my body of course I know that I put on weight ! Body shaming is not for those who are fat or chubby, but also for those who are thin. Those who are thin also going through body shaming. "You're so thin, do you even eat?" "You dont have boobs or ass, not nice la your body shape"! What the fuck is wrong with this society man ?! Like seriously, fat also problem, thin also problem; so you people expect all the 7.7 billion human being in this world to be in perfect size???? Body-shaming manifests in many ways:

1) Criticizing your own appearance, through a judgment or comparison to another person. (eg: “I’m so ugly compared to her.” “Look at how broad my shoulders are.”) 2) Criticizing another’s appearance in front of them, (eg: “With those thighs, the short dress ain't gonna look nice on you .”) 3) Criticizing another’s appearance without their knowledge. (eg: “Did you see what she’s wearing today? Not flattering.”) When the photographers approached me to do this photoshoot they asked me to wear sleeveless blouse, when I heard that I hesitated for a bit! Because I do have broad shoulders, fat arms which not flattering at all! But one thing I asked myself was IF NOT NOW, THEN WHEN? So I said okay to this concept and did the shoot!! I'm so proud of myself that I stopped doubting on myself and my body!

text:
MAHIRA (39) ist Muslimin und lebt in Mumbai. „Als unverheiratete Frau spüre ich schon den Druck der Gesellschaft. Aber ich möchte mich diesem Heiratsdruck nicht hingeben, nur weil es Tradition ist. Familie kann man auf so unterschiedliche Weise leben. Ich könnte mir auch vorstellen, ein Kind zu adoptieren, oder ein fremdes Kind zu unterstützen.“ Ihre Eltern haben ihr nie Vorschriften gemacht, sich auf eine bestimmte Weise zu verhalten, nur weil es im Koran steht. Sie sagten immer: „Folge Deiner Religion, aber benutze auch Deinen eigenen Kopf.“ Nach dem Tod ihres Bruders hat sie nach etwas gesucht, was ihr Freude bereitet und landete beim Bauchtanz. Sie kündigte ihren Job als Store Managerin und unterrichtet seitdem andere Frauen darin.

Wann warst Du das letzte Mal glücklich?

Meine Nichte (14) kam am selben Tag zur Welt wie mein Bruder, der vor 10 Jahren bei einem Autounfall starb. Die beiden teilten eine wunderbare Verbindung. Immer wenn ich meine Nichte sehe, sehe ich auch meinen Bruder. Das macht mich glücklich.

Was müsste in Deinem Leben passieren, damit Du häufiger Glück erlebst?

Ich habe innerhalb kurzer Zeit die Geburt meiner Nichte und den Tod meines Bruders und meines Vaters erlebt. Das hat mich sehr verändert. Heute bin ich ein sehr viel zufriedenerer Mensch. Und wenn Unzufriedenheit aufkommt, versuche ich, nicht daran festzuhalten, sondern sie einfach wieder gehen zu lassen.

Was müsste in Indien passieren, damit die Menschen dort glücklicher zusammenleben? Und wie sieht Dein Beitrag aus?

Wir brauchen unbedingt mehr Bildung. Außerdem sollten wir Frauen uns viel stärker in der Politik engagieren, anstatt uns darüber zu beklagen, dass wir in diesem Land nur Bürger zweiter Klasse sind. Meinen Beitrag sehe ich darin, die Frauen in meinen Bauchtanz-Klassen zu ermutigen, sich so zu akzeptieren, wie sie sind. Ich möchte ihnen Selbstbewusstsein mitgeben.
.
Ich freue mich über Eure Kommentare🙏
.
👉www.drei-fragen-glueck.de
.
.

Ich könnte mir auch vorstellen, ein Kind zu adoptieren, oder ein fremdes Kind zu unterstützen.“ Ihre Eltern haben ihr nie Vorschriften gemacht, sich auf eine bestimmte Weise zu verhalten, nur weil es im Koran steht. Sie sagten immer: „Folge Deiner Religion, aber benutze auch Deinen eigenen Kopf.“ Nach dem Tod ihres Bruders hat sie nach etwas gesucht, was ihr Freude bereitet und landete beim Bauchtanz. Sie kündigte ihren Job als Store Managerin und unterrichtet seitdem andere Frauen darin.

Wann warst Du das letzte Mal glücklich?

Meine Nichte (14) kam am selben Tag zur Welt wie mein Bruder, der vor 10 Jahren bei einem Autounfall starb. Die beiden teilten eine wunderbare Verbindung. Immer wenn ich meine Nichte sehe, sehe ich auch meinen Bruder. Das macht mich glücklich.

Was müsste in Deinem Leben passieren, damit Du häufiger Glück erlebst?

Ich habe innerhalb kurzer Zeit die Geburt meiner Nichte und den Tod meines Bruders und meines Vaters erlebt. Das hat mich sehr verändert. Heute bin ich ein sehr viel zufriedenerer Mensch. Und wenn Unzufriedenheit aufkommt, versuche ich, nicht daran festzuhalten, sondern sie einfach wieder gehen zu lassen.

Was müsste in Indien passieren, damit die Menschen dort glücklicher zusammenleben? Und wie sieht Dein Beitrag aus?

Wir brauchen unbedingt mehr Bildung. Außerdem sollten wir Frauen uns viel stärker in der Politik engagieren, anstatt uns darüber zu beklagen, dass wir in diesem Land nur Bürger zweiter Klasse sind. Meinen Beitrag sehe ich darin, die Frauen in meinen Bauchtanz-Klassen zu ermutigen, sich so zu akzeptieren, wie sie sind. Ich möchte ihnen Selbstbewusstsein mitgeben.
.
Ich freue mich über Eure Kommentare🙏
.
👉www.drei-fragen-glueck.de
.
.

Один из самых часто задаваемых вопросов мне, когда где-то мелькают мои небритые части тела - это "А что твой парень об этом думает

repost: dopelada ⠀
⠀
И этот вопрос прямо демонстрирует то, как относятся к телам девушек. ⠀
⠀
Редко как к чему-то, что принадлежит им самим. Можно далеко не ходить - посмотрите на рекламу.
⠀
"Будь ухоженной для своего мужчины!
Мужчины на кости не бросаются.
Мужчинам нравятся _вот такие вот_ женщины!"
⠀
Все модификации с нашим телом нас учат пропускать через призму мужского взгляда: ⠀
⠀
а такая фигура мальчикам понравится? 
А этот макияж? 
А вот эта юбка?
А вот такая форма груди?
⠀
В какой-то момент мне начинает казаться, что если спросить девушку: "А тебе-то что самой нравится?" она не ответит. ⠀
⠀
Потому что она не смотрит на себя своими глазами. ⠀
⠀
Она пытается оценить себя мужскими.
⠀
У многих нет проблем с небритыми частями тела зимой - никто ведь не увидит. С растянутой и удобной одеждой дома, отсутствием макияжа - для кого делать это, если мне и так хорошо?
⠀
Но как только настало время выходить в люди, то многие стараются задвинуть своё "мне и так удобно" на второй план. ⠀
⠀
На первый план выходит "А на что людям будет приятно смотреть?".
⠀
И всем девушкам я сейчас хочу пожелать чаще смотреть на себя своими глазами, а не чужими. ⠀
⠀
И чаще думать о себе.

text:
Was ist wingwave? 🦋

Die Wingwave-Methode ist ein Leistungs- und Emotions-Coaching, das für den Coachee spürbar und schnell in wenigen Sitzungen zum Abbau von Leistungsstress und zur Steigerung von Kreativität, Mentalfitness und Konfliktstabilität führt. 
Wingwave-Coaching wird in den Bereichen Business, Leistungssport, Pädagogik und Didaktik, Gesundheit sowie in Künstlerkreisen erfolgreich genutzt. Oft wird die Methode mit anderen bewährten Coaching-Prozessen kombiniert.

1. Regulation von Leistungsstress (PSI = Performance Stress Imprinting) 
Effektiver Stressausgleich bei z.B.: sozialen Spannungsfeldern im Team oder mit Kunden, Rampenlicht-Stress, Nackenschlägen auf dem Weg zum Ziel, Flugangst oder bei körperlichem Stress wie z.B. Schlafmangel. Sie fühlen sich durch die rasche Stabilisierung Ihrer inneren Balance schnell wieder energievoll, innerlich ruhig und konfliktstark.

2. Ressourcen-Coaching 
Hier setzen wir die Interventionen für Erfolgsthemen wie Kreativitätssteigerung, Selbstbild-Coaching, überzeugende Ausstrahlung, positive Selbstmotivation, die Stärkung des inneren Teams, Ziel-Visualisierung und für die mentale Vorbereitung auf die Spitzenleistung ein - wie beispielsweise einen wichtigen Auftritt oder Sportwettkämpfe (in vivo-Coaching). 3. Belief-Coaching 
Leistungseinschränkende Glaubenssätze werden bewusst gemacht und in Ressource-Beliefs verwandelt. Von besonderer Bedeutung ist hier das Auffinden von Euphorie-Fallen im subjektiven Erleben, welche langfristig die innere Welt allzu erschütterbar machen könnten. Das Ziel ist eine emotional stabile Belief-Basis und persönliche Glaubenssätze, die auch anspruchsvollen mentalen Belastungen standhalten. ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ selbstbild

text:
After drastically losing 10 kgs within a span of a month, due to some health and mental sickness, here's what I have realised -
1. Body shaming happens to skinny people too.
2. It is very hard to gain weight.
3. When you are used to well fitted clothes, and suddenly nothing fits, it hurts.
4. Just as a person trying to lose weight, who's not happy with their body, we skinny people too get frustrated trying to do the opposite. 
5. Self love is awesome. No matter what body shape you have, embrace the beautiful creation that you are. Stay healthy and flaunt your body, however it is. Loving thyself is great! Ignoring all the negativity, have fun, eat whatever you wish. ❤
But everyone has a certain wish, make that happen for yourself and yourself only. Other's & negativity are not worth it. .
.

.
.
.
.

text:
'Wenn er dich so anguckt, ist er definitiv der Richtige.' Ich bin heute mal sehr ehrlich mit euch - ich hatte kein schönes Wochenende. Ich habe meine Familie besucht, expliziter, meinen Bruder, seine Frau und seine zwei Kids. Ich muss euch gestehen, dass ich kein sehr innige Verhältnis zu meinem Bruder pflege. Das hat viele Gründe, dessen Ausführungen ich hier weglasse, weil sie den Rahmen sprengen würden. Ich habe mich aber drauf eingelassen, weil ich ein gutes Herz habe und weil Familie mir wichtig ist. War keine gute Idee. Nicht nur die Stimmung, die teilweise sehr lieblos und kalt war, sondern insbesondere seine Aussagen zu meinem Gewicht haben mich sehr verletzt.

Ich hatte 2014-2015 abgenommen, bis ich irgendwann nur noch 72.5 kg gewogen habe. Ich habe mich dabei extrem unter Druck gesetzt, es lief alles sehr fix und ich war massiv unglücklich. Natürlich möchte ich jetzt auch wieder abnehmen, aber diesmal gesünder. Mein Bruder hat mich an diesem Wochenende darauf angesprochen und mit direkt gesagt, dass ich mich gehen gelassen habe. Und er fragte mich, wieso ich nicht weiter so schlank geblieben wäre. Ich habe es ihm versucht zu erklären, aber er wollte es nicht verstehen. Ich war sehr gekränkt, habe ich mich doch mit dem Minus am Freitag auf einem sehr guten Weg gefühlt. Es ging mit weiteren Sprüchen bzgl des Essens weiter, das ganze Wochenende. Er gab zu, dass er ein gestörtes Verhältnis zum Essen habe, und er ist schon sehr arg dünn (er war früher mal übergewichtig, jetzt kratzt er am Untergewicht). Ich weiß, dass er in seinem Sinne nicht verstehen kann, dass ich wieder zugenommen habe und dass ich mich nicht wohl gefühlt habe, als ich 'schlanker' war (btw, ich habe mich damals wahnsinnig dick gefühlt), tat es trotzdem weh. Und deswegen war ich so froh, als mein Freund am gestrigen Abend kam und mich durch das restliche Wochenende begleitet hat. Er liebt mich, ganz genau wie ich bin. Und er zeigt es mir, in so vielen Arten und Weisen.

Worte können nicht beschreiben, was mir dieser Mann bedeutet. Und wie dankbar ich ihm für solche Momente bin. ❤ Ily.

text:
Hai semua, cuma pengen sedikit bisa diblng curcol wkwk. 
Jadi, gue itu sbnrnya jrng mau diajak foto. Karna apa ya, gue pasti mati gaya gitu wkwk. Gue mau foto kdng kalo tempatnya kyk jrng aja gue temuin gitu. Kalo orng abis foto biasanya pasti dipost di IG/Status WA kan? Sama, gue jg. 
Tapi, ada lho yg bikin orng jd males bahkan malu ngepost foto mereka ke sosmed karena komentar dari kalian yg ngeliat postingan itu. Bbrp hari yg lalu gue ngepost foto gue di SG&SWA. Trus ada yg komen:“Kok makin gendut sih, Jla?”“Gede bngt sih badannya?”“Belom tinggi jg deh lu.”“Gak malu Jla, makin gendut? Gak ada niatan diet?”“Kok iteman sih skrng?” Mungkin bagi lo yg komen biasa aja karna nyampein opini lo, tp tau gak kalo opini lo itu bikin orng yg lo komenin itu sakit hati? Gue sih orngnya Alhamdulillah bngt sabodoamat sama omongan orng. Gak peduli, tp secuek²nya orng kalo diusik jg lama² risih. 
Emang kenapa sih? Emang ganggu lo? Emang gue makan, minta duit dari lo? Emang gue numpang hidup sama lo? Gak kan? Jadi gak ush deh komen kyk gitu, gak cuma ke gue, ke semua orng. Selagi lo gak keluar duit bakal hidup gue, jd lo gak ada hak buat ngurusin hidup gue. 
Tangan sama mulu dijaga, nnt kalo didoain jelek sama orng yg lo komentarin trus dikabulin Allah, mampus lo. Makin dewasa bukannya makin dijaga, malah makin jadi kyk sampahnya. Kalo lo ngerasa kyk ada perubahan di orng itu, cukup lo blng sama diri lo sendiri aja. Gak ush disampein ke orngnya, malah bikin sakit hati. Gak cewek gak cowok sama aja. Hati² aja lo. Ntar dibalikin, nangis² lo! 
Duh udh ah. Ntar makin kmn² haha. Cerpen lg deh. Santai, gue gak bakalan sebut nama kalian yg berhasil ngusik ketenangan hidup gue. Jd gak bakalan diserang sama manusia² lainnya. Baikkan gue, pdhl jari sama mulut kalian jahat sama gue ehehehe.
